<% content_for :title, "Cookie Policy - Dealo" %>
<div class="static-page">
  <div class="container static-page-container">
    <h1 class="static-page-title">Cookie Policy</h1>
    <div class="static-page-content">
      <p class="static-lead">This page explains how Dealo uses cookies and similar technologies.</p>

      <section class="static-section">
        <h2>What are cookies?</h2>
        <p>Cookies are small text files stored on your device when you visit a website. They help the site remember your preferences and keep you signed in.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="static-section">
        <h2>Cookies we use</h2>
        <ul class="static-list">
          <li><strong>Strictly necessary</strong> — Required for the site to work (e.g. security, signing in). These cannot be switched off.</li>
          <li><strong>Functional</strong> — Remember your choices (e.g. language, region) to improve your experience.</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics</strong> — Help us understand how visitors use Dealo so we can improve the service (e.g. page views, clicks).</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="static-section">
        <h2>Managing cookies</h2>
        <p>You can control or delete cookies via your browser settings. Blocking certain cookies may affect how the site works (for example, you may need to sign in again each time).</p>
      </section>

      <section class="static-section">
        <h2>Updates</h2>
        <p>We may update this cookie policy from time to time. The “Last updated” date at the top will change when we do.</p>
      </section>

      <p>For more on how we use data, see our <%= link_to "Privacy Policy", privacy_policy_path, class: "static-link" %>. Questions? <%= link_to "Contact us", contact_path, class: "static-link" %>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
